It is not necessary, hints the Bishop, that we consider Jonah as tombed in the 
whale’s belly, but as temporarily lodged in some part of his mouth. And this 
seems reasonable enough in the good Bishop. For truly, the Right Whale’s 
mouth would accommodate a couple of whist-tables, and comfortably seat all the 
players. Possibly, too, Jonah might have ensconced himself in a hollow tooth; 
